reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 30, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Adds counter work space
reviews.reviewText: I love these. I have had one with round bars, but prefer these with square bars. They add extra work space, great when cleaning vegetable's, you don’t need a dish drying rack and they fold back when not in use. I have giving 6 other people these racks and they LOVE to them too.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 29, 2023
reviews.reviewText: This is a great product. I love the way it is made and love the silverware holder. I do not like having a dish drainer on my cabinet and this is perfect for just a few dishes that I don’t put in my dishwasher. It is heavy enough that it stays put and doesn’t slide off your sink. Would buy again for sure.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 24, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars If I could rate more than 5 stars I would
reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. I struggled with 3 different drying racks over the years that just didn't do the trick. Either the cross bars would come out when a pan was placed on it, or they would start to rust a few months in. This silicone covered drying rack is so much better. Sanitary, I can easily disinfect it knowing there is no where it can rust! It dries perfectly as well and fits in a drawer if you don't want to leave it over the sink! We leave it, it matches our countertop really well!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 1, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars A good buy for the kitchen
reviews.reviewText: It’s a nifty kitchen accessory for those who are seeking the work station like function like myself with their kitchen sinks. I would recommend it is quite sturdy as time go on I would see how long this remains the same.I would highly recommend it to assist in having additional surface or a drying area on your sink in the kitchen.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 30, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars READ THE DIMENSIONS! It's great, but only for small sinks.
reviews.reviewText: Having used a couple different types of over-the-sink, roll-up dish drainers, I came to Amazon to find one that also incorporated a utensil holder. I was excited to see this model because: 1. It is totally silicone coated; 2. It has flat rather than round slats; and 3. It has a small, built-in utensil cup. The problem is, it is just 1/4" too short to span our kitchen sink. I noted before purchasing that it is only 12" wide, but I failed to consider the depth, thinking it would fit a standard sink. Alas, it doesn't. I would love if this company made a similar version of this same item that is just an inch deeper - then it would work for me and check all the boxes on my wish list.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Love the wrapped silicone to prevent rust
reviews.reviewText: We bought this for RV and it was one of the best purchases. Not only can you dry dishes on it including a place for your silverware, but you can also have an extra space to put a hot dish. It rolls up as well to allow use of that other sink if you need it. Love it!
